<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-82-0822 </DOCNO><TEXT>Outlines the principles of automatic coal winning technology in surfacemines employing bucket wheel excavators and belt conveyors and the possiblitiesand limits of computerized control. The role of automatic control ofexcavator advance and its slewing angle as well as the role of the cuttingspeed and depth of cut is considered from the standpoint of maximum output.Basic elements of coal cutting in various cutting techniques were analyzedand the possibility of their use in the automation of production wasconsidered. 10 figs.</TEXT></DOC>